====Transitive verb====
{{en-verb2|'''help'''|'''[[helps]]'''|'''[[helped]]''' ''or'' (''archaic'') '''[[holp]]'''|'''[[helped]]''' ''or'' (''archaic'') '''[[holpen]]'''|'''[[helping]]'''}}

#{{transitive}} To provide [[assistance]] to (someone or something).
#:''He '''helped''' his grandfather.''
#:''He '''helped''' his grandfather cook breakfast.''
#:''He '''helped''' cook breakfast.''
#:''They invited us to take as much food as we wanted, so I '''helped''' myself to some fruit.''
#{{transitive}} To contribute in some way to.
#:''The white paint on the walls '''helps''' make the room look brighter.''
#{{intransitive}} To provide assistance.
#:''I could see she was struggling to carry both her groceries and the baby, so I offered to '''help'''.''
#{{transitive}} To [[avoid]]; to [[prevent]]; to [[refrain]] from; to [[restrain]] (oneself).  (Usually with ''"cannot"'' or with ''"can"'' and a negative as in the ''"...if I can help it"'' example.)
#:''We couldn't '''help''' noticing that you were late.''
#:''She is trying not to smile, but she can't '''help''' it.''
#:''She is trying not to smile, but she can't '''help''' herself.''
#:''That player won't make a goal today if I can '''help''' it.''

